\setdisplaytitle{Colimit of Cofinal Subdiagrams}

Suppose there is a subdiagram inclusion \(\mathcal J \hookrightarrow \mathcal D\), or more generally just a functor. By being [[Cofinal-Subdiagram|cofinal]], the two diagrams give equivalent notions of cocones and colimits, purely \emph{by virtue of its shape}.

{{Cocone-of-Cofinal-Subdiagrams-Equivalence}}
